[2;36m                    [0m         hierarchy.                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Key observations                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. The failure originates in Jazzer’s `FilePathTraversal.check` logic, which      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         enforces safe file output.                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. The sanitizer is invoked via `processFileOutputStartHook` in                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FilePathTraversal`.                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. The stack trace shows the issue occurs during embedded document extraction in  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Tika’s CLI:                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded`                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `PackageParser.parseEntry` → `parseEntries` → `_parse` → `parse`             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - Up through the composite and auto-detect parsers.                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. The fuzzer harness [1m([0m`TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer`[1m)[0m calls `TikaCLI.main` or its       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         internal parse routines as the entry point, but is not the root cause.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Code areas to investigate                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. Jazzer’s `FilePathTraversal` sanitizer [1m([0mespecially `check`, `checkFile`,       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `processFileOutputStartHook`[1m)[0m.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. Apache Tika’s file extraction pipeline:                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor`                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `PackageParser` [1m([0mmethods `parseEntry`, `parseEntries`, `_parse`[1m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `AutoDetectParser` and `CompositeParser` layers.                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. Any file-output or temporary-directory handling logic in Tika that constructs  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         output paths based on archive entry names.                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. The harness in `TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer` to understand how inputs are passed to  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Tika and ensure the sanitizer is triggered correctly.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:74[0m[1m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:54[0m[1m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: ea76e639355e804b                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         An embedded-document extraction routine in Apache Tika’s CLI was flagged by Jazzer  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         as a “File path traversal” vulnerability when unpacking archive entries whose       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         normalized names contained “..” segments. To harden against traversal, a patch      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         replaced naive `new [1;35mFile[0m[1m([0mextractDir, normalizedName[1m)[0m` logic with a `Path`-based     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         resolution and an explicit check that the resolved path remains under `extractDir`, [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         throwing an `IOException` on failure. After applying the patch, the build fails     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         because the newly thrown `IOException` is neither caught nor declared in the        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         surrounding method’s signature.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - During fuzzing, Jazzer’s `FilePathTraversal` sanitizer detected that TikaCLI’s [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         embedded-document extractor was creating output files using `new [1;35mFile[0m[1m([0mextractDir,   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         normalizedName[1m)[0m` without sufficient normalization.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A path like `[35m/tmp/.../../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m` bypassed the intended extract    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         directory, triggering a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal`          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exception.                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace pointed to                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaCLI$[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` as the site where the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         unchecked file path was constructed.                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The patch replaces the old file-creation block with:                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • A call to `[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.resolve[0m[1m([0mnormalizedName[1m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • A check that the resulting `Path` still starts with `[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • An explicit `throw new [1;35mIOException[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` if the check fails                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Conversion back to `File` for downstream code                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Preserving the UUID-prefixing logic for existing files                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - In diff form, the changes around line [1;36m1157[0m of `TikaCLI.java` look like this:   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```diff                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                [35m/[0m[35m/[0m old:                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -      File outputFile = new [1;35mFile[0m[1m([0mextractDir, normalizedName[1m)[0m;                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -      if [1m([0m[1;35moutputFile.exists[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m … [1m}[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -      return outputFile;                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +      Path normalizedPath = [1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +          [1;35m.resolve[0m[1m([0mnormalizedName[1m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +          [1;35m.normalize[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +      if [1m([0m![1;35mnormalizedPath.startsWith[0m[1m([0m[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        throw new [1;35mIOException[0m[1m([0m[32m"Invalid embedded entry name: "[0m + normalizedName[1m)[0m;   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +      [1m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +      File outputFile = [1;35mnormalizedPath.toFile[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +      if [1m([0m[1;35moutputFile.exists[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m … [1m}[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +      return outputFile;                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Result                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Compilation fails with:                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              unreported exception java.io.IOException; must be caught or declared to be     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         thrown                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - This indicates the modified code now throws `IOException` inside a method that [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         neither declares `throws IOException` nor catches it locally.                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The method signature of the embedding extraction helper in `TikaCLI.java`      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         needs updating to propagate or handle `IOException`.                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Call sites of this helper [1m([0me.g., `parseEmbedded`,                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `processFileOutputStartHook`[1m)[0m must be reviewed for exception compatibility.         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Downstream logic that relies on the returned `File` may need to distinguish    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         between a failed path-validation exception and other I/O errors.                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Similar file-creation routines elsewhere in the Tika CLI should be audited for [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         consistent normalization and exception handling.                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
